{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"2278ad14-cb15-4200-87cf-862097dbd198","content":"This is a known .NET breaking change: **`DSA.Create()` throws `PlatformNotSupportedException` on macOS** (and other Apple platforms).\n\n## What happened\n\nApple's native crypto libraries (`Security.framework` / `CryptoKit`) **do not support DSA**. When .NET dropped its OpenSSL-based shim on macOS, there's no longer a platform provider for DSA, so `DSA.Create()` throws at runtime. Windows and Linux still have native DSA providers (CNG and OpenSSL respectively), so they continue to work.\n\n## How to fix it\n\n**Option 1 – Use BouncyCastle for legacy verification only** (recommended if you just need to verify old signatures):\n\n```bash\ndotnet add package BouncyCastle.Cryptography\n```\n\n```csharp\nusing Org.BouncyCastle.Crypto.Parameters;\nusing Org.BouncyCastle.Security;\n\nbool VerifyDsaSignature(byte[] publicKeyBytes, byte[] message, byte[] signature)\n{\n    var keyParam = (DsaPublicKeyParameters)PublicKeyFactory.CreateKey(publicKeyBytes);\n    var verifier = SignerUtilities.GetSigner(\"SHA-1withDSA\"); // or SHA-256withDSA\n    verifier.Init(forSigning: false, keyParam);\n    verifier.BlockUpdate(message, 0, message.Length);\n    return verifier.VerifySignature(signature);\n}\n```\n\nThis is pure managed code — works on all platforms with no native dependencies.\n\n**Option 2 – Migrate to a modern algorithm** (recommended long-term):\n\nRe-sign with **ECDsa** or **Ed25519**, which are supported everywhere:\n\n```csharp\nusing var ecdsa = ECDsa.Create(ECCurve.NamedCurves.nistP256);\nbyte[] sig = ecdsa.SignData(message, HashAlgorithmName.SHA256);\n```\n\n**Option 3 – Platform guard** (if you can tolerate macOS not verifying):\n\n```csharp\nif (!OperatingSystem.IsMacOS())\n{\n    using var dsa = DSA.Create();\n    // verify...\n}\n```\n\n## Recommendation\n\nIf this is a verification-only scenario for legacy data, go with **BouncyCastle** for an immediate cross-platform fix, then plan a migration to ECDsa/Ed25519 so you can drop the DSA dependency entirely.","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"53ce614b-0ef6-41d9-99cf-582783dd71a4","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"The user is asking about a .NET compatibility issue with DSA (Digital Signature Algorithm) on macOS after upgrading from .NET 10 to .NET 11. Let me think about what I know about this topic.\n\nThis is a known breaking change in .NET. Starting with .NET 7+, Microsoft has been progressively removing support for older/less-secure cryptographic algorithms. Specifically:\n\nIn .NET 7, DSA on macOS was already problematic because macOS's Security.framework (via Apple's CommonCrypto/CryptoKit) doesn't natively support DSA. Previously, .NET used OpenSSL on macOS for DSA operations, but there have been changes around this.\n\n\nThe real issue is that starting in .NET 7, `DSA.Create()` throws `PlatformNotSupportedException` on macOS since Apple's native crypto libraries don't support DSA and Microsoft removed the OpenSSL shim that previously enabled it. So if the user is seeing this error after upgrading to .NET 11, it's likely they were already hitting this limitation in .NET 7 or later, unless something else changed in their setup. on a real .NET breaking change where `DSA.Create()` throws `PlatformNotSupportedException` on macOS because Apple's crypto libraries don't support DSA. This was introduced back in .NET 7, so it would already be broken on .NET 10. Either the user's scenario is slightly off, or there's a newer breaking change between .NET 10 and .NET 11 that I'm not aware of given the May 2026 timeframe.\n\nThe most relevant issue is that Apple's native crypto frameworks don't provide DSA support, and when .NET removed the managed DSA implementation that relied on OpenSSL, the API started throwing this exception on macOS. The practical fix would involve either switching away from DSA or finding an alternative approach that doesn't depend on the platform's native crypto implementation.","outputTokens":1728,"requestId":"B41C:1E6FAE:90E777:B297D6:6A013563"},"id":"3ceb3d54-4279-4649-adbb-86bedfed5494","timestamp":"2026-05-11T01:48:54.763Z","parentId":"dda3b4c2-4317-4eda-960e-16915aefbcab"}
